art%20of%20my%20job.%20I%20was%20often%20the%20liaison%20between%20international%20clients%20and%20the%20team%20in%20China%2C%20helping%20everyone%20understand%20each%20other%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20create%20project%20teams%20with%20a%20local%20project%20leader%20to%20get%20their%20input%20on%20workflow%20and%20communication%20changes%2C%20and%20I%20made%20sure%20my%20colleagues%20had%20ownership%20over%20the%20new%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-from-sydney-australia-to-canada-pros-cons-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emoved%20from%20Australia%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20UK%2C%20I'd%20already%20experienced%20cultural%20differences%20in%20the%20workplace.%20I%20learned%20to%20be%20sensitive%20to%20people's%20different%20perspectives%20and%20that%20differences%20aren't%20always%20obvious.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20time%20to%20build%20trust%20with%20colleagues%20in%20China.%20Generally%2C%20the%20Australian%20style%20of%20work%20communication%20is%20very%20direct%2C%20so%20I%20had%20to%20adapt%20my%20style%20to%20slow%20down%2C%20listen%2C%20and%20spend%20more%20time%20building%20relationships%3Cstrong%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20respected%20that%20people%20would%20approach%20things%20differently%20and%20ensured%20they%20felt%20I%20was%20standing%20up%20for%20their%20perspective.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2233900abe-1a2d-42a3-8ab3-f321d68c7277%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EEmployees%20in%20China%20were%20very%20conscious%20of%20their%20place%20in%20the%20company%20hierarchy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHierarchies%20were%20very%20apparent%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-work-culture-love-hate-relationship-tech-worker-relocation-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChinese%20work%20culture%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20meetings%2C%20people%20deferred%20to%20their%20managers.%20It%20was%20unusual%20for%20a%20more%20junior%20employee%20to%20contribute.%20I%20had%20to%20really%20encourage%20them%20to%20speak%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJob%20titles%20mattered%20a%20lot%2C%20and%20people%20expected%20career%20progression.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20our%20global%20company%20was%20trying%20to%20flatten%20its%20organizational%20structure%20and%20we%20had%20to%20explain%20this%20would%20not%20work%20in%20China.%20Instead%2C%20we%20created%20a%20different%20structure%20with%20three%20sub-levels%20so%20people%20could%20feel%20they%20were%20progressing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20also%20placed%20a%20lot%20of%20importance%20on%20things%20like%20office%20size%2C%20what%20the%20view%20from%20their%20office%20was%20like%2C%20and%20having%20a%20corner%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20time%20to%20overcome%20this%20deep%20desire%20to%20respect%20hierarchy.%20To%20promote%20change%2C%20I%20spoke%20to%20people%20one-on-one%20as%20much%20as%20possible.%20I'd%20find%20any%20opportunity%20to%20ask%20colleagues%20questions%20directly%20and%20try%20to%20build%20a%20rapport.%20I'd%20often%20sit%20in%20the%20open-plan%20area%2C%20which%20most%20people%20in%20my%20position%20wouldn't%20have%20done.%20I%20think%20it%20made%20me%20more%20approachable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c0b621e4-2b76-4d33-914f-bb32d89ad9e4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EPeople%20were%20less%20transparent%20about%20struggling%20with%20the%20work%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20difference%20I%20noticed%20was%20that%20no%20one%20raised%20issues%20in%20meetings%20if%20a%20project%20wasn't%20going%20well.%20You%20might%20eventually%20find%20out%20about%20a%20problem%20behind%20closed%20doors%2C%20but%20getting%20the%20issue%20out%20in%20the%20open%20was%20challenging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20a%20client%20once%20wanted%20to%20hire%20scientists%20with%20a%20very%20specific%20background%20in%20a%20remote%20location.%20From%20the%20start%2C%20our%20team%20knew%20it%20would%20be%20virtually%20impossible%2C%20but%20they%20didn't%20share%20this%20concern%20until%20the%20delivery%20dates%20started%20to%20slip%20and%20the%20client%20got%20worried.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffamily-and-parenting-flawed-western-world-2018-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWestern%20cultures%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it's%20more%20likely%20%E2%80%94%20although%20not%20a%20given%20%E2%80%94%20that%20the%20concerns%20or%20issues%20would%20be%20flagged%20earlier.%20In%20China%2C%20people%20seemed%20to%20take%20pride%20in%20their%20work%20and%20I%20think%20they%20didn't%20want%20to%20make%20themselves%20look%20bad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20found%20that%20nobody%20would%20tell%20me%20about%20the%20problem%20until%20it%20got%20to%20the%20point%20where%20I%20had%20to%20have%20awkward%20conversations%20with%20clients%20because%20we%20were%20behind.%20As%20a%20Westerner%2C%20I%20quickly%20needed%20to%20learn%20that%20what%20was%20not%20being%20said%20was%20also%20important.%20I%20had%20to%20be%20more%20receptive%20to%20subtle%20cues%20and%20never%20make%20assumptions%20without%20clarifying%20with%20a%20colleague%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e124bf2b-3db8-43e6-aa4b-49aaae2b5e5e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EPeople%20on%20my%20team%20weren't%20as%20used%20to%20actioning%20direct%20orders%20as%20they%20were%20in%20the%20West%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDelegating%20tasks%20often%20took%20more%20time%20and%20explanation%2C%20from%20my%20experience.%20If%20you%20asked%20somebody%20in%20a%20Western%20country%20to%20take%20on%20a%20project%2C%20you%20might%20say%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20need%20100%20people%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20month%20in%20these%20jobs%2C%20off%20you%20go.%26quot%3B%20In%20China%2C%20I%20would%20sit%20down%20with%20people%20and%20work%20out%20a%20detailed%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20my%20colleagues%2C%20I%20had%20to%20spell%20out%20exactly%20what%20I%20wanted%20in%20a%20way%20I'd%20never%20experienced.%20One%20of%20my%20more%20experienced%20Chinese%20colleagues%2C%20who'd%20done%20a%20lot%20of%20work%20with%20global%20companies%2C%20mentioned%20that%20it%20could%20be%20because%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-teacher-china-differences-education-schools-students-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeducation%20system%20in%20China%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20said%20schools%20didn't%20give%20students%20as%20much%20latitude%20to%20do%20things%20in%20their%20own%20way%20as%20they%20did%20in%20the%20West.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it%20could%20also%20just%20have%20been%20that%20the%20team%20I%20was%20working%20with%20in%20China%20lacked%20experience%20in%20doing%20larger-scale%20recruitment%2C%20so%20they%20didn't%20have%20the%20confidence%20to%20make%20detailed%20plans.%20Once%20the%20plan%20was%20there%2C%20the%20team%20was%20incredibly%20committed%20to%20delivering%20the%20results.%20My%20peers%20were%20really%20diligent%20and%20had%20an%20incredible%20work%20ethic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222808e45e-7794-4b70-8a05-0a4534a3dfb4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWorking%20in%20a%20new%20culture%20gave%20me%20more%20confidence%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20came%20back%20to%20the%20UK%20in%202018%2C%20and%20having%20seen%20the%20terrible%20impact%20of%20plastic%20rubbish%20in%20Asia%2C%20I%20started%20my%20own%20business%2C%20KIND2%20%E2%80%93%20we%20make%20solid%20shampoo%20bars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20time%20in%20Asia%20was%20a%20really%20interesting%20chapter%20in%20my%20life.%20It%20gave%20me%20more%20confidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20anybody%20has%20the%20chance%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frto-has-won-in-asia-workers-returning-to-office-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ework%20in%20Asia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I'd%20recommend%20it.%20There%20were%20many%20moments%20when%20things%20were%20more%20difficult%20than%20if%20I'd%20been%20doing%20it%20in%20a%20familiar%20culture%2C%20but%20I%20wouldn't%20trade%20it%20for%20a%20second.%3C%2F