ow%2F111255617.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Tommy%20Robinson%20arrested%20in%20Canada%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719310740000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F06%2F1920x1080%2Fskynews-protest-tommy-robinson_6571112.jpg%3F20240601145750%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Ftommy-robinson-arrested-over-immigration-offence-in-canada-13158512%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Far-right%20activist%20Tommy%20Robinson%20has%20been%20arrested%20in%20Canada%20on%20suspicion%20of%20an%20immigration%20offence.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A80%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Ftommy-robinson-arrested-over-immigration-offence-in-canada-13158512%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Explained%3A%20What%20Makes%20Korean%20Ramen%20So%20Delicious%20And%20Yet%20Dangerous%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20Denmark%2C%20over%20safety%20concerns%2C%20recalled%20several%20ramen%20products%20manufactured%20by%20South%20Korean%20company%20Samyang.%20Reports%20say%20these%20noodles%20contain%20dangerously%20high%20levels%20of%20capsaicin%2C%20a%20compound%20found%20in%20chilli%20peppers.%20The%20three%20products%20pulled%20from%20the%20market%20included%20the%20Buldak%203x%20Spicy%20%26amp%3B%20Hot%20Chicken%2C%20the%202x%20Spicy%20%26amp%3B%20Hot%20Chicken%2C%20and%20Hot%20Chicken%20Stew.%20Danish%20authorities%20said%20the%20high%20spice%20levels%20could%20pose%20a%20risk%20of%20'acute%20poisoning'%20to%20consumers%2C%20especially%20children%20and%20adults%20with%20health%20disorders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESamyang%20has%20disputed%20these%20claims%20and%20said%20the%20spices%20in%20their%20ramen%20products%20were%20within%20acceptable%20limits.%20Nonetheless%2C%20Denmark's%20move%20is%20significant%20as%20it%20comes%20against%20the%20burgeoning%20popularity%20of%20Korean%20noodles%20across%20the%20world%2C%20including%20India.%20The%20controversy%20also%20brings%20to%20light%20cultural%20differences%20in%20spice%20tolerance%20and%20food%20habits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESteeped%20In%20K-Culture%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKorean%20culture%20started%20gaining%20popularity%20in%20India%20around%202020.%20That%20year%2C%20the%20Netflix%20viewership%20of%20K-dramas%20and%20K-pop%20had%20recorded%20a%20year-on-year%20jump%20of%20a%20whopping%20370%25.%20This%20coincided%20with%20a%20corresponding%20rise%20of%20162%25%20in%20the%20import%20of%20Korean%20food%20products.%20%C2%A0According%20to%20data%20collected%20by%20consumer%20intelligence%20firm%20NielsenIQ%2C%20the%20size%20of%20the%20Korean%20noodles%20market%20surged%20multi-fold%20from%20Rs%202%20crore%20in%202021%20to%20over%20Rs%2065%20crore%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20makes%20these%20noodles%20so%20popular%3F%20Some%20say%20it's%20ingredients%20like%20rice%2C%20noodles%2C%20vegetables%2C%20meat%2C%20sesame%20oil%2C%20chilli%2C%20pepper%2C%20soy%2C%20and%20spices.%20Common%20in%20both%20Korean%20and%20Indian%20cuisines%2C%20perhaps%20they%20make%20Korean%20food%20feel%20familiar%20to%20Indian%20consumers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20originating%20in%20Japan%2C%20instant%20ramen%20has%20today%20come%20to%20be%20South%20Korea's%20soul%20food.%20It%20can%20be%20had%20for%20breakfast%2C%20lunch%2C%20or%20dinner%2C%20and%20prepared%20at%20home%20or%20ordered%20at%20restaurants.%20It%20can%20even%20be%20packed%20as%20a%20quick%20meal%20for%20long%20travels.%20According%20to%20the%20World%20Instant%20Noodle%20Association%2C%20a%20South%20Korean%20person%20consumes%20around%2077%20servings%20of%20instant%20noodles%20a%20year%20on%20average%2C%20second%20only%20to%20Vietnam%20at%2085.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20South%20Korean%20instant%20ramen%20is%20a%20spicy%2C%20flavourful%20alternative%20for%20people%20in%20countries%20whose%20traditional%20cuisines%20may%20be%20relatively%20less%20savoury.%20Recently%2C%20the%20stock%20price%20of%20Samyang%20Foods%20soared%2070%25%20after%20its%20Buldak%20carbonara%20ramen%20went%20viral%20on%20TikTok.%20The%20product%20became%20so%20popular%20in%20the%20US%20that%20shelves%20quickly%20went%20empty.%20In%20fact%2C%20a%20video%20that%20showed%20a%20young%20Texas%20girl%20receiving%20a%20multi-pack%20of%20Buldak%20carbonara%20ramen%20as%20a%20birthday%20gift%20amassed%2014%20million%20views%20and%202.7%20million%20likes%20within%2022%20hours.%20Even%20celebrities%20like%20Cardi%20B%20wanted%20a%20taste%20of%20Buldak%2C%20whose%20products%20are%20exported%20to%20as%20many%20as%2040%20countries.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20doctors%20caution%20against%20the%20risks%20of%20consuming%20extremely%20spicy%20foods%2C%20especially%20packaged%20products%20like%20instant%20ramen.%20%26quot%3BIn%20a%20country%20where%20people%20struggle%20with%20metabolic%20disorders%20from%20an%20early%20age%2C%20these%20instant%20foods%20should%20be%20either%20avoided%20or%20be%20an%20occasional%20treat%20only.%20Reading%20the%20ingredients%20on%20the%20back%20label%20will%20open%20your%20eyes%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20nothing%20in%20them%20is%20good%20for%20your%20health.%20Additives%2C%20preservatives%2C%20colours%2C%20flavours%2C%20emulsifiers%2C%20etc%2C%20can%20pose%20long-term%20risks%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Dr%20Shalini%20Singhal%2C%20a%20nutritionist%20who%20runs%20a%20diet%20and%20wellness%20clinic%20in%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECapsaicin%2C%20a%20common%20component%20in%20many%20global%20cuisines%2C%20can%20lead%20to%20inflammation%20and%20irritation%20in%20the%20digestive%20tract%20if%20consumed%20in%20high%20quantities%2C%20resulting%20in%20symptoms%20like%20abdominal%20pain%2C%20diarrhoea%20and%20vomiting.%20%26quot%3BRamen%20noodles%20contain%20carbohydrates%20and%20are%20poor%20in%20fibre%20or%20protein.%20The%20noodles%20also%20have%20high%20salt%20content%2C%20and%20all%20these%20can%20lead%20to%20nutritional%20problems%20like%20weight%20gain.%20Salt%20could%20cause%20high%20blood%20pressure.%20Lacking%20in%20protein%2C%20instant%20ramen%20also%20does%20not%20satiate%20your%20hunger%20and%20can%20lead%20to%20overeating%20and%20obesity.%20Excess%20spice%20in%20any%20food%20is%20a%20gastric%20irritant%2C%20causing%20a%20host%20of%20problems%20like%20hyperacidity%2C%20gastritis%20and%20acid%20reflux%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Dr%20Anirban%20Chatterjee%2C%20senior%20gastroenterologist%20and%20hepatologist%2C%20CMRI%20and%20Woodlands%20Hospital%2C%20Kolkata.%20Health%20experts%20point%20out%20that%20consuming%20instant%20noodles%20two%20or%20more%20times%20a%20week%20is%20associated%20with%20cardiometabolic%20syndrome%2C%20increasing%20the%20likelihood%20of%20developing%20high%20triglycerides%20and%20suffering%20heart%20disease%2C%20diabetes%2C%20or%20stroke.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20governments%20and%20regulatory%20authorities%20in%20many%20countries%20are%20now%20waking%20up%20to%20the%20risks%2C%20India%20has%20yet%20to%20act.%20Beyond%20legal%20safeguards%2C%20what's%20important%20is%20that%20consumers%20themselves%20make%20informed%20decisions%20about%20their%20dietary%20habits%20and%20prioritise%20their%20health%20and%20well-being.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719310680000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-12%2F8316m0e_chilli-oil-ramen_625x300_19_December_22.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffood%2Fkorean-noodles-spice-it-up-but-with-caution-5966204%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Recently%2C%20Danish%20authorities%20banned%20a%20brand%20of%20Korean%20noodles%2C%20citing%20the%20extremely%20high%20spice%20levels%20that%20could%20pose%20a%20risk%20of%20'acute%20poisoning'%20to%20consumers%2C%20especially%20children%20and%20adults%20with%20health%20disorders.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffood%2Fkorean-noodles-spice-it-up-but-