es.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20reached%20out%20to%20the%20green%20activist%2C%20earlier%20known%20for%20his%20innovative%20methods%20to%20harvest%20rainwater%2C%20to%20understand%20the%20nuances%20of%20water%20scarcity%20in%20India%20and%20how%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F351304%2Fchennai-bengaluru-water-crisis-prashant-sharma-grey-water-recycling-in-schools%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eone%20can%20use%20greywater%20%3C%2Fa%3Ein%20daily%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EWhat%20is%20greywater%20and%20why%20reuse%20it%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20heart%20of%20the%20issue%20of%20water%20shortage%20lies%20in%20the%20disproportionate%20use%20of%20potable%20water%20%E2%80%94%20a%20staggering%2098%20percent%20of%20water%20supplied%20to%20Indian%20homes%20is%20used%20for%20purposes%20other%20than%20drinking%20and%20cooking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20should%20understand%20that%20only%20two%20percent%20of%20the%20water%20supplied%20to%20our%20homes%20is%20used%20for%20drinking%20and%20cooking.%20The%20remaining%2098%20percent%2C%20used%20for%20non-drinking%20purposes%2C%20can%20always%20be%20catered%20to%20through%20recycled%20and%20filtered%20water%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20points%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20urban%20habits%2C%20such%20as%20using%20fresh%20water%20for%20toilet%20flushing%2C%20contribute%20extensively%20to%20water%20wastage.%20%E2%80%9CFlushing%20alone%20gulps%20down%2035%20percent%20of%20a%20typical%20household%E2%80%99s%20water%20consumption%2C%20prompting%20experts%20to%20advocate%20for%20the%20use%20of%20greywater%20and%20underground%20saline%20water%20for%20these%20purposes%2C%20especially%20in%20cities%20like%20Mumbai%20where%20groundwater%20quality%20is%20infamously%20poor%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22